statement:
For each of the following multiple-choice questions, there is one
correct answer. Circle the corresponding (roman) numeral.

a) Use the graph of g(x) below to determine the correct set of values of
$\displaystyle G(x) = \int_{0}^{x}g(t)\,dt$

\begin{figure}[htbp]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=.5\textwidth]{MATH103April2006Q1a.jpg}
\caption{MATH103April2006Q1a.jpg}
\end{figure}

i.

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}llllll@{}}
x & 0 & 2 & 4 & 6 & 8
\\
G(x) & 0 & 2 & 4 & 1 & 0
\end{longtable}

ii.

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}llllll@{}}
x & 0 & 2 & 4 & 6 & 8
\\
G(x) & 0 & -2 & -2 & 0 & 4
\end{longtable}

iii.

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}llllll@{}}
x & 0 & 2 & 4 & 6 & 8
\\
G(x) & 2 & 0 & 0 & 2 & 2
\end{longtable}

iv.

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}llllll@{}}
x & 0 & 2 & 4 & 6 & 8
\\
G(x) & 0 & 2 & -2 & 0 & 4
\end{longtable}
